entry.title: Russian Forces Push Into Key City in East Ukraine
entry.content: The fight for Severodonetsk, one of the last Ukrainian strongholds in the eastern Donbas region, underscores the central role of artillery in the war.

entry.title: Bombed Bridges, Closed Ports Keep Ukrainian Grain From a World That Needs It
entry.content: Across Ukraine, farmers are navigating mines, traversing bombed bridges and risking dangerous maneuvers at overworked ports to circumvent a Russian blockade and get their grains to a world desperate for them.
